title: How to Make Money Online Reselling Free Items
headline: Learn how to build and sustain a profitable online business reselling free products in this free online course.
description: Did you know you could get free products online and then resell them for a profit? This course will introduce you to the rebate arbitrage business model. We will demonstrate how and where to acquire free products using website tutorials. You will learn to navigate online marketplaces and discover business strategies for growth. If building another source of income is your goal, then here's your chance. Sign up today!

courseDescription:
Everyone loves free stuff, but what if you could earn a regular income reselling free products? This course by Stoneriver is designed to take you step by step through the business process and shows you, with clear examples, how to access free items and resell them for a profit. Absolute beginners, as well as experienced entrepreneurs, can benefit from the lessons.

Websites that offer free items seek to rank their products higher on Amazon and so give free goods in exchange for reviews and initial sales. Explore how to get these free items and then discover the marketplaces where you could sell them. See the ‘Resource’ section of the course for a list of cashback websites to utilise. When selling online, it is important to consider the type of product and the most suitable marketplace in order to maximise profit.

We go even further to discuss selling tips and strategies that you can immediately begin to implement so that your products get visibility and become in-demand. The start-up costs using this model are low and the risks minimal, so anyone can set it up easily, eventually scaling up to a full-time business. If you would like an extra stream of income so you can live on your own terms, enrol in this course and start learning today!

  • Lesson Summary - Cashback Arbitrage

  • Key lessons to take away:

    • Cashback arbitrage refers to a business where you get cashback for products and then sell the products to make money.
    • The website offering the cashback does this so that a new product can rank higher on the selling site - often Amazon.
    • Amazon houses and sells products, making money from the selling fee or the Fulfillment By Amazon service.
    • You, the consumer benefits from the business model, because you get free products to use or sell.
    • With coupon arbitrage, the seller will give you a coupon to buy a product at a very low price on Amazon, which you can then resell for the full price.
    • With cashback Arbitrage, the seller will give you a full refund or a nearly full refund of what you spent for the product on Amazon.
    • Depending on the cashback site, it will take anywhere between 48 hours to 35 days to get your cashback.
    • You can also make even more money using amazon credit cards; when you use the Discover It card or Amazon Store Card with 5% cash back for purchases on Amazon, you can make the extra 5% of the money you spent on the free items.
    • If you plan on scaling your business, then it makes sense to use the Amazon Cards to make extra money.
